CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 2, 1966, pg. 12A, reads: "To the Victor - Schenley's Ed Gibson looks around for a pair of scissors as he attempts to cut down the nets after Schenley wrapped up the state high school basketball championship.  Gibson, as things turned out, never cut down the nets, but the Schenley team ended up getting both sets later on.  That's Kenny Durrett in foreground... Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Schenley High School basketball player Ed "Pete" Gibson attempting to cut net, with Kenny Durrett in foreground, after winning state championship against Chester, Civic Arena
